      "description": "Validation of CFD model sensitivity predictions for component dimensional variations (±0.1 mm impeller clearance, ±0.05 mm volute gap). Simulation results assessed against in-house experimental hemolysis measurements for three geometric variants. High assurance declared based on breadth of parameter space explored and consistency of trend predictions across all variants.",
      "passedCriteria": true,
      "quantitativeResult": "Trend prediction accuracy 94% across 12 geometric configurations; RH ratio correctly ranked in 11 of 12 cases"
    }
  ],
